            <div class="step step-1" id="step-1">
                <div class="step-content">
                    <p>As the climate warms, new data shows huge swaths of land across the globe are quickly <span
                            class="red-text">drying</span>, threatening humanity’s supply of fresh water.</p>
                    <div class="legend">
                        <div class="legend-gradient"></div>
                        <div class="legend-labels">
                            <p class="label gradient-start-label" id="gradient-start-label">0</p>
                            <p class="label gradient-end-label" id="gradient-end-label">>2</p>
                            <p class="label gradient-label" id="gradient-label">Water Loss (mmSLE)</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step step-2" id="step-2">
                <div class="step-content">
                    <p>In the far north, the detected loss is due largely to glaciers melting and subarctic lakes
                        drying.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step step-3" id="step-3">
                <div class="step-content">
                    <p>But farther south — where most people live — it is largely the race to suck groundwater from
                        aquifers that is removing the water from the continents.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step step-4" id="step-4">
                <div class="step-content">
                    <p>So much groundwater is now being pumped that it is filling the oceans as it drains off land,
                        becoming one of the largest drivers of global sea level rise.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
