        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/texas-flooding-inaction-state-legislature">
                                    Texas Lawmakers Largely Ignored Recommendations Aimed at Helping Rural Areas Like Kerr County Prepare for Flooding
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Texas lawmakers’ inaction on flood prevention often hits rural and economically disadvantaged communities the hardest, experts said.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
                        <span class="story-card__byline-author">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/lexi-churchill">Lexi Churchill</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/lomi-kriel">Lomi Kriel</a>, <a href="https://www.propublica.org/texas">ProPublica and The Texas Tribune</a>,
